extremeRemoteSyslogServerTable.description: This table is used to configure remote syslog servers and contains information on the same.

extremeRemoteSyslogServerAddressType.name: extremeRemoteSyslogServerAddressType
extremeRemoteSyslogServerAddressType.description: The type of address specified in the object 'extremeRemoteSyslogServerAddress'. Currently, only 'ipv4' and 'dns' are supported.

extremeRemoteSyslogServerAddress.name: extremeRemoteSyslogServerAddress
extremeRemoteSyslogServerAddress.description: The address of the remote syslog server. This can be a DNS name or an IPv4 address.

extremeRemoteSyslogServerPort.name: extremeRemoteSyslogServerPort
extremeRemoteSyslogServerPort.description: The UDP port number of the remote syslog server to which syslog messages will be sent.

extremeRemoteSyslogServerFacility.name: extremeRemoteSyslogServerFacility
extremeRemoteSyslogServerFacility.description: The facility which will be sent in all syslog messages to this remote syslog server.

extremeRemoteSyslogServerSeverity.name: extremeRemoteSyslogServerSeverity
extremeRemoteSyslogServerSeverity.description: The syslog message severity. All syslog messages of the specified severity for which the Bits are set, will be sent to this syslog server. When setting this object in a 'createAndGo' request, all lower bits upto and including the desired bit position must be set. For example, if bit info(4) needs to be set then bits critical(0), error(1), warning(2), notice(3) and info(4) must also be set in the request. Consequently, all syslog messages of a given severity and higher will be sent to the syslog server. It is not possible to send messages that match only a few selected non-contiguous severities.

It is not possible to change the values of the objects of a row once it has been created, except by 'destroy'ing and re-creating the row.
